summary: XAP2 is a novel hepatitis B virus X-associated protein that inhibits X transactivation. The study was conducted at the University of Texas Health Science Center in San Antonio. It was published in the Journal of Molecular and Cell Biology. For confidential support call the National Suicide Prevention Lifeline at 1-800-273-8255 or visit www.suicidepreventionlifeline.org.
